3. Features and capabilities
Grouped by Q2C sub-domain. Each capability is tagged [must] (required for Aerostack to operate the practice), [should] (required before scale past ~$5M ARR), or [later] (post-scale or product-packaging concern).
3.1 Product / offering catalog
[must] Three solution-line taxonomy (S1 Revenue Growth / S2 Cost Deflation / S3 SaaS Launch; reserve S4 Data & AI Governance per architecture one-pager).
[must] Marketplace offering definitions (~20–30 SKUs) with: pricing model, fulfillment pod type, default terms, AWS funding eligibility, rev-rec treatment hint.
[must] Pricing model support: fixed-fee, T&M, subscription (flat), subscription (tiered), usage-based, hybrid (flat + usage).
[must] Periodicity support: one-time, monthly, quarterly, annual, custom (e.g., "first year flat, then 5% escalator").
[must] Versioned catalog — catalog version pinned to contract at execution; in-flight quotes refresh on demand; active contracts are immutable against future catalog changes.
[should] Bundle templates — pre-composed engagement lifecycles (e.g., "MAP Assessment → Modernize → LaunchLogic Scale") sellers can start from.
[should] Band-tier presets (Band 1 / 2 / 3) that pre-fill sensible defaults based on deal size.
[later] Customer-specific catalog overlays (for large strategic accounts with their own SKU lists).
3.2 Quote construction (CPQ)
[must] Guided deal builder: pick solution line → pick offerings → configure scope → see price.
[must] Multi-stage quote representation: one quote can contain VALIDATE + BUILD + OPERATE line items with different rev-rec treatments.
[must] Real-time total calculation including AWS funding offset preview.
[must] Quote versioning and redline comparison (seller iterates with customer).
[must] Approval routing with SLA and escalation.
[should] Quote-to-proposal generation (PDF / docx) branded per partnership (enterprise, GGTC, joint).
[should] Margin view (internal only) showing cost vs. price per line item.
[later] AI-assisted quote suggestions based on similar prior deals.
3.3 Contracts
[must] Contract template library per offering with variable insertion.
[must] E-signature integration (DocuSign or similar).
[must] Amendments and change orders linked to parent contract (not standalone new contracts).
[must] Activation gate: a contract can require a delivery-system signal ("implementation accepted") before billing starts.
[must] Multi-party signature flows — customer + enterprise + Graphite where joint delivery.
[should] Term management: renewal dates, auto-renew flags, notice periods, escalator schedules.
[should] Clause library for common custom terms (free months, discount windows, price protection).
[later] Contract-as-data (parsed, queryable clauses) for compliance and AI-driven renewal prep.
3.4 Order and fulfillment hand-off
[must] On contract activation, generate an order record handed to the appropriate delivery team (assessment pod, BUILD pod, LaunchLogic ops, CSP ops).
[must] Order contains: scope, milestones, acceptance criteria, billing triggers, referenced contract ID.
[must] Delivery systems post back milestone completion signals that Aerostack uses to trigger invoicing or OPERATE activation.
[should] Capacity check at order stage — flag if the assigned pod is over-committed in the relevant band.
3.5 Billing and invoicing
[must] Generate invoices per contract billing rules (periodic, milestone-based, consumption-based).
[must] Metered usage ingest from One-CT (CSP consumption) and cost-opt reporting.
[must] AWS funding offset application on invoices (net-of-funding view to customer; full-fee view internally until claim approved).
[must] Multi-entity, multi-currency invoicing (enterprise US, potential EU/APJ entities for ISV partners).
[must] Proration on mid-period start, stop, or tier change.
[should] Collections workflow: dunning sequences, AR aging, escalation.
[should] Credit note / refund handling with audit trail.
[later] Customer-facing invoice portal with self-serve history and payment.
3.6 Revenue recognition inputs
[must] Every line item tagged with rev-rec category: one-time fixed, one-time milestone-based, recurring ratable, usage point-in-time, bundle-allocated.
[must] Allocation hints for bundles (e.g., VALIDATE + BUILD + OPERATE commitment) — finance decides the final allocation but Aerostack provides the building blocks.
[must] Change-order impact on rev-rec recalculation.
[should] Export to accounting (NetSuite or equivalent) with rev-rec schedule.
3.7 Channel / partner economics
[must] Partner-of-record assignment per account (Graphite via TD Synnex OR enterprise via Ingram).
[must] Managed resell margin calculation on cloud consumption (distributor-dependent: 7–10% default).
[must] Tiered referral calculation on managed services revenue for sourced accounts (1% baseline → 5% strategic).
[must] Channel reassignment with forward-only effect (prior invoices preserve original attribution).
[should] Distributor statement reconciliation (TD Synnex and Ingram both post statements — reconcile against Aerostack-computed margin).
[should] AWS program attribution (MAP, IWA, IWB, EBA) per deal for co-sell tracking.
3.8 Practice-level reporting
[must] Practice MRR calculation per the partnership definition (OPERATE recurring + resale margin on enterprise-sourced accounts, excluding one-time BUILD/VALIDATE).
[must] Step-down trigger monitoring ($250K / $500K / $1M Practice MRR, 2 consecutive months).
[must] Revenue split views per engagement stage for GGTC/enterprise reporting.
[must] Band 1/2/3 ramp tracking against KPI targets (pipeline, ARR, active CSP accounts, active BUILD engagements).
[should] Cohort analysis (accounts by source, by entry offering, by progression through stages).
[should] Pipeline-to-revenue funnel with conversion rates per stage.
3.9 Cross-cutting
[must] Audit log on every pricing, contract, and billing change.
[must] Role-based access — sellers see their deals, partners see their attributed accounts, investors see aggregated views only.
[must] API-first so the CRM, delivery systems, and billing vendor integrate cleanly.
[should] Sandbox / preview mode for pricing changes before they hit live catalog.
[later] GRC-sensitive deployment model — customer-tenant vs. enterprise-tenant deployment option (this is a repackaging concern from the transcript's customer conversation).

4. Data model (core entities)
Relationships described narratively; a formal ERD follows in v0.2.
4.1 Commercial entities
Account — the customer. Attributes: legal name, entities (parent / billing / delivering), industry, source (enterprise / Graphite / distribution / direct), partner-of-record, AWS account IDs, Azure tenant IDs, channel flags.
Opportunity — the deal-in-progress (mirrored from CRM; Aerostack holds the commercial shaping layer on top). Attributes: solution line, band tier, expected stage sequence, AWS funding eligibility, target close.
Offering — catalog SKU. Attributes: solution line, pricing model, default terms, rev-rec category, fulfillment pod type, AWS funding eligibility, versioned.
Quote — a commercial proposal for an opportunity. Composed of quote line items, each referencing a versioned Offering with configured scope. A quote has lifecycle: draft → in approval → presented → accepted → expired/superseded.
Contract — an executed quote (or amended contract). Locks the catalog version. Contains terms (payment, renewal, termination, custom clauses). Points to one or more Orders.
Amendment / Change Order — modification to a Contract. Preserves history.
4.2 Fulfillment entities
Order — delivery-layer instantiation of a contract's obligations. One Contract can produce multiple Orders (e.g., one VALIDATE order + one BUILD order + one OPERATE subscription). Each Order has its own fulfillment pod and lifecycle.
Milestone — gated step in an Order. Triggers billing and/or OPERATE activation.
Subscription — an OPERATE-type Order with recurring term, tier, and metering configuration.
Usage Event — metered consumption record (CSP consumption, cost-opt findings, etc.). Ingested from One-CT or cloud provider.
4.3 Financial entities
Invoice — issued charge. Tied to one Contract, one or more Orders/Subscriptions, and specific line items.
Payment — inbound money. Tied to Invoices.
Credit Note — refund or adjustment.
Funding Claim — AWS MAP/EBA/IWA/IWB claim. Tied to Contract and specific line items. Status: submitted / approved / denied.
Rev-Rec Line — normalized revenue recognition schedule output. Tied to Invoice line item.
4.4 Channel / partner entities
Channel — managed resell channel (TD Synnex via Graphite, Ingram via enterprise, others as they come online). Attributes: distributor, reseller, default margin band, SPP status.
Referral — tiered referral computed on an OPERATE revenue line for a sourcing party. Attributes: source party, % tier, monthly amount, payout status.
4.5 Practice / reporting entities
Practice MRR Snapshot — monthly computed figure per the partnership definition. Used for investor reporting and step-down triggers.
Band Tracking Record — Band 1/2/3 KPI measurement per month against targets.
4.6 Cross-cutting
Audit Event — every create/update on pricing, contract, billing carries an audit event (actor, before/after, reason).
Approval — approval request + decision + approver per routing rule.

